    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>6, Queen Anne St.</placeName>
                    <date>Wednesday night </date>
                    <seg type="supplemental">(tomorrow I return to Down)<ref target="#foot.f2"/></seg>
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Murray</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have just received a note from Mr. Dallas, saying he is pressed for money, will you be so very kind as to settle at once with him.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>As I am in the begging line I will take the opportunity of begging for a few copies of new Edit. of the Descent; and pray kindly inform me as soon as ever copies are <hi rend="underline">nearly</hi> ready, that I may communicate with you.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>I have just returned the 4 slightly corrected sheets to Messrs. Clowes; so I shall cause no delay.<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>I hear flattering accounts from indirect, and therefore trustworthy, sources about the Book.</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the dates of CD’s stay in London and by the reference to proofs for the second issue of <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> (see nn. 2 and 4, below). In 1871, 1 March fell on Wednesday.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD stayed in London with his brother <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1211.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Erasmus Alvey Darwin</ref> from 23 February until 2 March 1871 (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1179.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Sweetland Dallas</ref> had prepared the index for <hi rend="italic">Descent.</hi> His note has not been found; see, however, <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 19, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7480.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to R. F. Cooke, 10 February [1871]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">Murray was printing a second issue of the first edition of <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 19, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7519.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 27 February [1871]</ref>). CD’s presentation list for <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> has six names written on the verso that may have been for the second printing (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 19, Appendix IV).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_979.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Clowes &amp; Sons</ref> were the printers of <hi rend="italic">Descent.</hi> Murray had asked CD to send corrected sheets at once (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 19, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7519.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 27 February [1871]</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
